data.title: Don Quichotte (Don Quixote) (Furnishing Fabric)

thumbnail.alt_text: A work made of cotton, plain weave; copperplate printed.

data.artist_display:
Possibly after design by Jean Jacques Lagrenèe le Jeune (French, 1739–1821) after engravings by Charles Nicolas Cochin l'Aîné (French, 1688–1754), Magdaleine Hortenels Cochin (French, 1683–1767), Jean Baptiste Haussard (French, 1679/80–1749), and Louis Silvestre l'Aîné (French, 1664–1740)
Based on paintings by Charles Antoine Coypel (French, 1694–1752)
France, Nantes
